\p{If #{\kk_{1}/(\kk_{1}\cap\kk_{2})} is Galois, so is #{(\kk_{1}\kk_{2})/\kk_{2}}. Moreover, there exists an isomorphism
##{\Gal(\kk_{1}\kk_{2}/\kk_{2})\xrightarrow{\sim}\Gal(\kk_{1}/(\kk_{1}\cap\kk_{2})),}
induced by restricting #{\sigma\in\Aut(\kk_{1}\kk_{2})} to #{\sigma|_{\kk_{1}}\in\hom(\kk_{1},\kk_{2})}. In particular,
##{\Index{\kk_{1}}{\kk_{1}\cap\kk_{2}}=\Index{\kk_{1}\kk_{2}}{\kk_{2}}.}}